# BamSignal Production Rules

You are working on BamSignal production code.

BamSignal is a Nigerian-first social discovery platform.
The product is already in launch-stabilization mode.

Your job is to behave like a careful production engineer.

====================================================
ABSOLUTE RULES
====================================================

- Do not redesign locked member UI unless explicitly asked.
- Do not touch unrelated files.
- Do not “improve” things outside the task.
- Do not create duplicate auth, signup, onboarding, payment, or route systems.
- Do not guess.
- Inspect first, then patch.
- Every fix must include evidence:
  - root cause
  - files changed
  - why each file changed
  - commands run
  - test results
- Never stage unrelated dirty files.
- Never commit generated APK/AAB/dist files unless explicitly requested.
- Never hide build warnings.
- Never claim success if tests were not run.
- If a test cannot be run, say why.
- If unsure, stop and ask.

====================================================
PROJECT LOCKS
====================================================

The following rules are locked unless the user explicitly overrides them:

- Member UI is frozen except bug fixes.
- Compact fintech design system must be preserved.
- Auth is username + PIN only.
- Login must never mention email or password.
- Signup may collect email/phone for verification, but login is username + PIN.
- Public pages must never trigger member restore.
- Home must never render onboarding.
- Onboarding must only render at /onboarding.
- Completed users must go to /home.
- Incomplete users must go to /onboarding.
- Payments must return users to their original app page.
- Paystack callbacks must never dump users on the public homepage.
- BamSignal must send purchase confirmation emails after successful payments.
- Android release must verify fresh web assets before AAB/APK build.
- SEO/public pages must not affect member app routes.
- Photo upload must be upload-first unless a true technical upload failure occurs.
- Admin routes must remain separate from member routes.
- Generated files must not be committed unless explicitly requested.

====================================================
ROUTING RULES
====================================================

Public routes:
- /
- /blog
- /cities
- /nigeria
- /help
- /safety
- /features
- /premium
- /faq
- /guides
- /compare
- legal/public pages

Public routes must not show:
- Restoring your account
- onboarding
- member dashboard
- member shell

Member routes:
- /home
- /discover
- /chats
- /signals
- /profile
- /settings
- /subscription

Member routes must not render:
- public homepage
- SEO layout
- onboarding inside /home

Onboarding route:
- /onboarding

Only /onboarding renders onboarding.

====================================================
AUTH RULES
====================================================

Login UI:
- Username
- PIN
- Login

Do not show:
- Username or email
- Email login
- Phone login
- Password
- Reset password

Use:
- Forgot PIN
- Reset PIN
- Invalid username or PIN

Backend may keep compatibility field names if needed, but user-facing copy must say PIN.

====================================================
PAYMENT RULES
====================================================

Before redirecting to Paystack, preserve:
- paymentReturnPath
- paymentProductType
- paymentProductId
- paymentReference
- paymentStartedAt

After successful verification:
- activate product
- send BamSignal purchase email once
- redirect to preserved return path
- never public homepage unless no better fallback exists

====================================================
ANDROID RELEASE RULES
====================================================

Before building AAB/APK:
- build web
- sync Capacitor
- verify Android assets match dist
- verify build marker
- verify service worker cache version
- fail loudly if stale

Never upload or reuse stale AAB.

====================================================
WORKFLOW FOR EVERY TASK
====================================================

1. Inspect first.
2. Identify root cause.
3. Patch the smallest safe fix.
4. Do not touch unrelated files.
5. Run required tests.
6. Check git status.
7. Stage only related files.
8. Commit with clear message.
9. Push only after tests pass.
10. Report changed files and test results.
11. Stop after the requested task.

====================================================
REQUIRED COMMANDS
====================================================

For normal code changes, run:

npm run build
npm run test:server-import

If Android assets are touched, also run:

npx cap sync android
npm run android:verify-assets

If SEO content is touched, also run:

npm run seo:validate

====================================================
GIT SAFETY
====================================================

Before every commit, run:

git status --short

Only stage files directly related to the task.

If unrelated dirty files exist:
- leave them unstaged
- mention them in the report

Do not stage:
- dist/
- APK files
- AAB files
- android/app/build/
- .gradle/
- random screenshots
- generated cache files
- unrelated SEO/photo/store leftovers

====================================================
REPORT FORMAT
====================================================

After every task, report:

- Root cause
- Files changed
- Why each file changed
- Commands run
- Test results
- Git status summary
- Commit hash
- Anything left unstaged and why

====================================================
STOP RULE
====================================================

Stop after the requested task.

Do not continue to the next fix unless the user says done or gives the next task.
